  <section style="padding-block: 80px;">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
        <h2>What students and parents <em>most often ask</em>.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What courses does Hartron Skill Centre Hisar offer?</summary>
          <p>We offer 25 NCVET-approved computer courses including CCA, CDA, Python, Java, Tally with GST, AutoCAD, Digital Marketing, Web Technology, PHP, Android Development, C, C++, Foundation Course (FC), CIFT, CCBA and more. <a href="courses.html">See all courses →</a></p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is the Hartron CCA certificate valid for government jobs?</summary>
          <p>Yes. Hartron's CCA (Certificate in Computer Applications) is NCVET-approved and grants exemption from the SETC (State Eligibility Test for Computers) written test for Haryana Government Clerk Post recruitment. Our other certificates are also recognized for government, banking, and private sector hiring.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do you provide placement assistance?</summary>
          <p>Yes — placement assistance is provided to all enrolled students. With our 20,000+ alumni network spanning government offices, banks, accounting firms, and IT companies across Haryana, we connect graduates to real job opportunities. Career counselling is also available throughout the course.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What are the eligibility requirements?</summary>
          <p>Eligibility varies by course. CCA and CDA: 11th Pass or 12th Pursuing. Most short-term courses are open to anyone with basic education. Beginner-friendly Foundation Course (FC) requires no prior knowledge. <a href="courses.html">Check specific course eligibility →</a></p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Where exactly is Hartron Skill Centre Hisar located?</summary>
          <p>We are located between Nagori Gate and Bus Stand, near Gurudwara in Hisar, Haryana 125001. Walk-in welcome during working hours (Monday–Saturday, 9 AM – 7 PM). Call <a href="tel:+919215838058">92158-38058</a> or <a href="tel:+919812086917">98120-86917</a> for directions.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Do students from nearby towns and villages also study here?</summary>
          <p>Absolutely. Students from Hansi, Adampur, Barwala, Uklana, Agroha, Narnaund, Bhuna, Balsamand, Sisai, Nalwa and surrounding villages within 40 km regularly join our courses. We offer morning, afternoon, and evening batches to accommodate students who commute.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What makes Hartron different from other private computer institutes?</summary>
          <p>Three things: <strong>Government recognition</strong> (NCVET + NSQF, not just private certification), <strong>27 years of proven track record</strong> (20,000+ alumni), and <strong>real job impact</strong> — most importantly, the SETC test exemption for Clerk Post that no private institute can offer.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
